title: Electronic Warfare Technician
description: Served as an Intelligence Analyst on a Control Ship, operating computer controlled electronic equipment used for detection, analysis, and identification of radar emissions. Responsible for the production, processing, analysis, reporting, classification and integration of: signals intelligence (SIGINT) and electronic signals intelligence (ELINT) into intelligence products. Also, was responsible for the daily training, leadership, health and welfare of seven sailors within my workspace. Responsible for operating systems that produce high-power electronic signals used to deceive and jam enemy electronic sensors, including those associated with electronically guided weapons. Responsible for interpreting incoming electronic signals to determine their source and location, utilizing computer databases to analyze the electronic intelligence received, allowing for a proper and time sensitive evaluation of weapon and detection system capabilities and limitations. Led multiple successful exercises as Control Ship in which our ship was recognized for timely and accurate analysis of the threat. Successfully led the EW Watch as Supervisor during deployment to Middle East in support of Operation Iraqi Freedom.
